[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":2062},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F17\u002Fday-3-your-first-nodejs-project\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F17\u002Fday-3-your-first-nodejs-project\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F17\u002Fday-3-your-first-nodejs-project\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F17\u002Fday-3-your-first-nodejs-project\u002F":2038,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F17\u002Fday-3-your-first-nodejs-project\u002F":2047},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20230917\u002F3753839802\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":2021,"date":2022,"description":2023,"extension":2024,"lang":2025,"meta":2026,"navigation":1753,"path":2027,"readingMinutes":2028,"seo":2029,"standalone":2030,"stem":2031,"tags":2032,"tldr":2035,"updated":2022,"url":2036,"__hash__":2037},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fday-3-your-first-nodejs-project.md","Day 3 - Your First Node.js Project","2181241943",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":2012},"minimark",[11,19,24,27,31,34,107,110,132,136,139,161,164,177,180,196,199,205,215,226,229,373,376,383,398,401,532,538,541,544,606,621,633,650,693,704,756,759,809,816,822,825,840,859,862,879,882,888,900,906,911,920,956,959,1047,1053,1067,1100,1141,1146,1197,1203,1274,1284,1294,1298,1301,1310,1313,1323,1368,1373,1643,1655,1658,1662,1665,1671,1674,1677,1680,1689,1693,1696,1699,1702,1715,1718,1931,1938,1976,1986,1989,1993,1996,2005,2008],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"First project","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fisray_notarray_first_project_93881759-5520-40f0-90b3-ff0d5f51ecc5.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26],{},"After two days of intro, we're finally about to build our first Node.js project. By now you should have a decent grasp of Node.js basics, so we can comfortably get started.",[20,28,30],{"id":29},"basic-terminal-commands","Basic terminal commands",[12,32,33],{},"First, I want you to memorize a few terminal commands. These are used constantly in real-world dev — even when you're using VSCode's terminal. I'm likely to use these in the article, so I want you to at least know:",[35,36,37,54,60,74,95,101],"ul",{},[38,39,40,44,45],"li",{},[41,42,43],"code",{},"cd [path]",": move to the specified path\n",[35,46,47],{},[38,48,49,50,53],{},"e.g., ",[41,51,52],{},"cd \u002FUsers\u002Fusername\u002FDesktop",": move to the desktop",[38,55,56,59],{},[41,57,58],{},"cd ..",": go up one folder",[38,61,62,65,66],{},[41,63,64],{},"mkdir [folder name]",": create a folder\n",[35,67,68],{},[38,69,49,70,73],{},[41,71,72],{},"mkdir my-project",": create a my-project folder",[38,75,76,79,80],{},[41,77,78],{},"touch [filename.ext]",": create a file\n",[35,81,82,88],{},[38,83,49,84,87],{},[41,85,86],{},"touch index.js",": create the index.js file",[38,89,90,91,94],{},"Note: Windows doesn't support this command, use ",[41,92,93],{},"echo > [filename.ext]"," instead",[38,96,97,100],{},[41,98,99],{},"ls",": list all files and folders in the current path",[38,102,103,106],{},[41,104,105],{},"ll",": list all files and folders in the current path (with detailed info)",[12,108,109],{},"These are the most basic and most common terminal commands. If you're not familiar with them, I'd suggest practicing and getting used to them — they're going to come up constantly in development.",[111,112,113],"blockquote",{},[12,114,115,119,120,123,124,127,128,131],{},[116,117,118],"strong",{},"Note","\nFile extension means the file's type. For example, ",[41,121,122],{},"index.js"," has the extension ",[41,125,126],{},".js"," and the main name ",[41,129,130],{},"index",". Operating systems often hide file extensions, so if you can't see them, you'll need to enable that in OS settings.",[20,133,135],{"id":134},"lets-talk-about-packagejson","Let's talk about Package.json",[12,137,138],{},"To get you more comfortable with the terminal, please try entering this:",[140,141,146],"pre",{"className":142,"code":143,"language":144,"meta":145,"style":145},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","mkdir example\n","bash","",[41,147,148],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,150,153,157],"span",{"class":151,"line":152},"line",1,[149,154,156],{"class":155},"s_sBn","mkdir",[149,158,160],{"class":159},"sTRMh"," example\n",[12,162,163],{},"Then move into the example folder:",[140,165,167],{"className":142,"code":166,"language":144,"meta":145,"style":145},"cd example\n",[41,168,169],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,170,171,175],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,172,174],{"class":173},"sCcAr","cd",[149,176,160],{"class":159},[12,178,179],{},"Now type this in the example folder:",[140,181,183],{"className":142,"code":182,"language":144,"meta":145,"style":145},"npm init -y\n",[41,184,185],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,186,187,190,193],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,188,189],{"class":155},"npm",[149,191,192],{"class":159}," init",[149,194,195],{"class":173}," -y\n",[12,197,198],{},"When you open this project in VSCode, it should look like this:",[12,200,201],{},[15,202],{"alt":203,"src":204},"package.json","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fnpm_init.png",[111,206,207],{},[12,208,209,211,214],{},[116,210,118],{},[41,212,213],{},"npm init -y"," is a quick way to create a package.json.",[12,216,217,218,221,222,225],{},"The above process is what we usually call \"initializing a project\" (usually we'd also ",[41,219,220],{},"git init",", but that's not the focus here, so I'm skipping it). We use ",[41,223,224],{},"npm init"," to initialize the project so we can install packages later. Why? Because all package info is written in package.json, so we have to initialize the project before installing packages.",[12,227,228],{},"You'll see a package.json file appear. Open it and you'll see:",[140,230,234],{"className":231,"code":232,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","{\n  \"name\": \"example\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"\",\n  \"main\": \"index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"test\": \"echo \\\"Error: no test specified\\\" && exit 1\"\n  },\n  \"keywords\": [],\n  \"author\": \"\",\n  \"license\": \"ISC\"\n}\n","json",[41,235,236,242,258,271,284,297,306,329,335,344,356,367],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,237,238],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,239,241],{"class":240},"sMAXC","{\n",[149,243,245,249,252,255],{"class":151,"line":244},2,[149,246,248],{"class":247},"sKpQp","  \"name\"",[149,250,251],{"class":240},": ",[149,253,254],{"class":159},"\"example\"",[149,256,257],{"class":240},",\n",[149,259,261,264,266,269],{"class":151,"line":260},3,[149,262,263],{"class":247},"  \"version\"",[149,265,251],{"class":240},[149,267,268],{"class":159},"\"1.0.0\"",[149,270,257],{"class":240},[149,272,274,277,279,282],{"class":151,"line":273},4,[149,275,276],{"class":247},"  \"description\"",[149,278,251],{"class":240},[149,280,281],{"class":159},"\"\"",[149,283,257],{"class":240},[149,285,287,290,292,295],{"class":151,"line":286},5,[149,288,289],{"class":247},"  \"main\"",[149,291,251],{"class":240},[149,293,294],{"class":159},"\"index.js\"",[149,296,257],{"class":240},[149,298,300,303],{"class":151,"line":299},6,[149,301,302],{"class":247},"  \"scripts\"",[149,304,305],{"class":240},": {\n",[149,307,309,312,314,317,321,324,326],{"class":151,"line":308},7,[149,310,311],{"class":247},"    \"test\"",[149,313,251],{"class":240},[149,315,316],{"class":159},"\"echo ",[149,318,320],{"class":319},"sWyjQ","\\\"",[149,322,323],{"class":159},"Error: no test specified",[149,325,320],{"class":319},[149,327,328],{"class":159}," && exit 1\"\n",[149,330,332],{"class":151,"line":331},8,[149,333,334],{"class":240},"  },\n",[149,336,338,341],{"class":151,"line":337},9,[149,339,340],{"class":247},"  \"keywords\"",[149,342,343],{"class":240},": [],\n",[149,345,347,350,352,354],{"class":151,"line":346},10,[149,348,349],{"class":247},"  \"author\"",[149,351,251],{"class":240},[149,353,281],{"class":159},[149,355,257],{"class":240},[149,357,359,362,364],{"class":151,"line":358},11,[149,360,361],{"class":247},"  \"license\"",[149,363,251],{"class":240},[149,365,366],{"class":159},"\"ISC\"\n",[149,368,370],{"class":151,"line":369},12,[149,371,372],{"class":240},"}\n",[12,374,375],{},"As mentioned, package.json is where we manage packages, so we use it to install them. Let's install our first package!",[12,377,378,379,382],{},"We'll start with ",[41,380,381],{},"nodemon"," — this package auto-restarts your code when you modify it, so you don't have to manually re-run every time.",[140,384,386],{"className":142,"code":385,"language":144,"meta":145,"style":145},"npm install nodemon\n",[41,387,388],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,389,390,392,395],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,391,189],{"class":155},[149,393,394],{"class":159}," install",[149,396,397],{"class":159}," nodemon\n",[12,399,400],{},"After installation, package.json becomes:",[140,402,404],{"className":231,"code":403,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \"name\": \"example\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"\",\n  \"main\": \"index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"test\": \"echo \\\"Error: no test specified\\\" && exit 1\"\n  },\n  \"keywords\": [],\n  \"author\": \"\",\n  \"license\": \"ISC\",\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"nodemon\": \"^3.0.1\"\n  }\n}\n",[41,405,406,410,420,430,440,450,456,472,476,482,492,503,510,521,527],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,407,408],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,409,241],{"class":240},[149,411,412,414,416,418],{"class":151,"line":244},[149,413,248],{"class":247},[149,415,251],{"class":240},[149,417,254],{"class":159},[149,419,257],{"class":240},[149,421,422,424,426,428],{"class":151,"line":260},[149,423,263],{"class":247},[149,425,251],{"class":240},[149,427,268],{"class":159},[149,429,257],{"class":240},[149,431,432,434,436,438],{"class":151,"line":273},[149,433,276],{"class":247},[149,435,251],{"class":240},[149,437,281],{"class":159},[149,439,257],{"class":240},[149,441,442,444,446,448],{"class":151,"line":286},[149,443,289],{"class":247},[149,445,251],{"class":240},[149,447,294],{"class":159},[149,449,257],{"class":240},[149,451,452,454],{"class":151,"line":299},[149,453,302],{"class":247},[149,455,305],{"class":240},[149,457,458,460,462,464,466,468,470],{"class":151,"line":308},[149,459,311],{"class":247},[149,461,251],{"class":240},[149,463,316],{"class":159},[149,465,320],{"class":319},[149,467,323],{"class":159},[149,469,320],{"class":319},[149,471,328],{"class":159},[149,473,474],{"class":151,"line":331},[149,475,334],{"class":240},[149,477,478,480],{"class":151,"line":337},[149,479,340],{"class":247},[149,481,343],{"class":240},[149,483,484,486,488,490],{"class":151,"line":346},[149,485,349],{"class":247},[149,487,251],{"class":240},[149,489,281],{"class":159},[149,491,257],{"class":240},[149,493,494,496,498,501],{"class":151,"line":358},[149,495,361],{"class":247},[149,497,251],{"class":240},[149,499,500],{"class":159},"\"ISC\"",[149,502,257],{"class":240},[149,504,505,508],{"class":151,"line":369},[149,506,507],{"class":247},"  \"dependencies\"",[149,509,305],{"class":240},[149,511,513,516,518],{"class":151,"line":512},13,[149,514,515],{"class":247},"    \"nodemon\"",[149,517,251],{"class":240},[149,519,520],{"class":159},"\"^3.0.1\"\n",[149,522,524],{"class":151,"line":523},14,[149,525,526],{"class":240},"  }\n",[149,528,530],{"class":151,"line":529},15,[149,531,372],{"class":240},[12,533,534,535,537],{},"You can see ",[41,536,381],{}," and its version got recorded in package.json, and your project also gained two new things: node_modules and package-lock.json. We'll talk about those later — first let's go through each property in package.json.",[12,539,540],{},"I mentioned package.json is where we manage packages — calling it the heart of NPM isn't an exaggeration, since we install, update, and remove packages through it. So this file is really important.",[12,542,543],{},"Quick rundown of each property currently in package.json:",[35,545,546,552,558,564,570,576,582,588,594,600],{},[38,547,548,551],{},[41,549,550],{},"name",": project name",[38,553,554,557],{},[41,555,556],{},"version",": project version",[38,559,560,563],{},[41,561,562],{},"description",": project description",[38,565,566,569],{},[41,567,568],{},"main",": project entry point",[38,571,572,575],{},[41,573,574],{},"scripts",": project commands",[38,577,578,581],{},[41,579,580],{},"keywords",": project keywords",[38,583,584,587],{},[41,585,586],{},"author",": project author",[38,589,590,593],{},[41,591,592],{},"license",": project license",[38,595,596,599],{},[41,597,598],{},"dependencies",": project dependencies",[38,601,602,605],{},[41,603,604],{},"devDependencies",": project dev dependencies",[111,607,608],{},[12,609,610,612,613,620],{},[116,611,118],{},"\npackage.json actually has more properties than these. If you want to know all the special ones, just check the ",[614,615,619],"a",{"href":616,"rel":617},"https:\u002F\u002Fdocs.npmjs.com\u002Fcli\u002Fv9\u002Fconfiguring-npm\u002Fpackage-json",[618],"nofollow","official npm package.json docs"," — there are way too many to list.",[12,622,623,624,626,627,629,630,632],{},"The three properties you really need to pay attention to are ",[41,625,598],{},", ",[41,628,604],{},", and ",[41,631,574],{},", since you'll definitely use these. Let's look at what they're for.",[12,634,635,636,638,639,642,643,645,646,649],{},"First, ",[41,637,574],{},". This property holds executable commands. For example, you can put a ",[41,640,641],{},"start"," command in ",[41,644,574],{}," so you can run it via ",[41,647,648],{},"npm start",". Here's how:",[140,651,653],{"className":231,"code":652,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"start\": \"node index.js\"\n  },\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n}\n",[41,654,655,659,665,671,681,685,689],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,656,657],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,658,241],{"class":240},[149,660,661],{"class":151,"line":244},[149,662,664],{"class":663},"sQrFR","  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n",[149,666,667,669],{"class":151,"line":260},[149,668,302],{"class":247},[149,670,305],{"class":240},[149,672,673,676,678],{"class":151,"line":273},[149,674,675],{"class":247},"    \"start\"",[149,677,251],{"class":240},[149,679,680],{"class":159},"\"node index.js\"\n",[149,682,683],{"class":151,"line":286},[149,684,334],{"class":240},[149,686,687],{"class":151,"line":299},[149,688,664],{"class":663},[149,690,691],{"class":151,"line":308},[149,692,372],{"class":240},[12,694,695,696,699,700,703],{},"You can change this command to whatever you want. For example, you could run ",[41,697,698],{},"nodemon index.js"," via ",[41,701,702],{},"npm run dev",":",[140,705,707],{"className":231,"code":706,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"start\": \"node index.js\",\n    \"dev\": \"nodemon index.js\"\n  },\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n}\n",[41,708,709,713,717,723,734,744,748,752],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,710,711],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,712,241],{"class":240},[149,714,715],{"class":151,"line":244},[149,716,664],{"class":663},[149,718,719,721],{"class":151,"line":260},[149,720,302],{"class":247},[149,722,305],{"class":240},[149,724,725,727,729,732],{"class":151,"line":273},[149,726,675],{"class":247},[149,728,251],{"class":240},[149,730,731],{"class":159},"\"node index.js\"",[149,733,257],{"class":240},[149,735,736,739,741],{"class":151,"line":286},[149,737,738],{"class":247},"    \"dev\"",[149,740,251],{"class":240},[149,742,743],{"class":159},"\"nodemon index.js\"\n",[149,745,746],{"class":151,"line":299},[149,747,334],{"class":240},[149,749,750],{"class":151,"line":308},[149,751,664],{"class":663},[149,753,754],{"class":151,"line":331},[149,755,372],{"class":240},[12,757,758],{},"So even naming it \"Agumon Evolution\" is totally fine:",[140,760,762],{"className":231,"code":761,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"start\": \"node index.js\",\n    \"Agumon Evolution\": \"nodemon index.js\"\n  },\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n}\n",[41,763,764,768,772,778,788,797,801,805],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,765,766],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,767,241],{"class":240},[149,769,770],{"class":151,"line":244},[149,771,664],{"class":663},[149,773,774,776],{"class":151,"line":260},[149,775,302],{"class":247},[149,777,305],{"class":240},[149,779,780,782,784,786],{"class":151,"line":273},[149,781,675],{"class":247},[149,783,251],{"class":240},[149,785,731],{"class":159},[149,787,257],{"class":240},[149,789,790,793,795],{"class":151,"line":286},[149,791,792],{"class":247},"    \"Agumon Evolution\"",[149,794,251],{"class":240},[149,796,743],{"class":159},[149,798,799],{"class":151,"line":299},[149,800,334],{"class":240},[149,802,803],{"class":151,"line":308},[149,804,664],{"class":663},[149,806,807],{"class":151,"line":331},[149,808,372],{"class":240},[12,810,811,812,815],{},"Just that to run it, you'd have to type ",[41,813,814],{},"npm run Agumon Evolution",".",[12,817,818],{},[15,819],{"alt":820,"src":821},"Agumon Evolution","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F1690725511276.gif",[12,823,824],{},"You might be wondering...",[12,826,827,828,830,831,833,834,830,837,839],{},"\"Why was the previous ",[41,829,641],{}," invoked with ",[41,832,648],{}," but ",[41,835,836],{},"dev",[41,838,702],{},"?\"",[12,841,842,843,846,847,849,850,853,854,856,857,815],{},"Mainly because npm provides some shortcut commands that don't need the ",[41,844,845],{},"run"," keyword — like ",[41,848,648],{}," and ",[41,851,852],{},"npm test",". But ",[41,855,702],{}," is something we defined ourselves, so it needs the ",[41,858,845],{},[12,860,861],{},"Here are the common shortcut commands:",[35,863,864,872],{},[38,865,866,868,869],{},[41,867,648],{},": runs ",[41,870,871],{},"npm run start",[38,873,874,868,876],{},[41,875,852],{},[41,877,878],{},"npm run test",[12,880,881],{},"These two are basically the most-used shortcuts.",[12,883,884,885,887],{},"Bonus tip: sometimes a project has lots of ",[41,886,574],{}," and you don't want to open package.json to check them all. You can use this:",[140,889,891],{"className":142,"code":890,"language":144,"meta":145,"style":145},"npm run\n",[41,892,893],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,894,895,897],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,896,189],{"class":155},[149,898,899],{"class":159}," run\n",[12,901,902],{},[15,903],{"alt":904,"src":905},"npm run","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fnpm_run.png",[12,907,908,909,815],{},"This lists all the ",[41,910,574],{},[12,912,913,914,916,917,919],{},"So far, you might think ",[41,915,574],{}," is done — nope. ",[41,918,574],{}," actually has something called \"Life Cycle Operation Order\", meaning scripts execute in a specific order. What's that order? Let me explain:",[12,921,922,923,926,927,626,930,629,933,936,937,939,940,942,943,942,945,947,948,950,951,629,953,955],{},"When you run ",[41,924,925],{},"npm run build",", if you've defined ",[41,928,929],{},"prebuild",[41,931,932],{},"build",[41,934,935],{},"postbuild"," in ",[41,938,574],{},", the execution order will be ",[41,941,929],{}," → ",[41,944,932],{},[41,946,935],{},". So ",[41,949,929],{}," runs before ",[41,952,932],{},[41,954,935],{}," runs after.",[12,957,958],{},"Quick example:",[140,960,962],{"className":231,"code":961,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"prebuild\": \"echo \\\"prebuild\\\"\",\n    \"build\": \"echo \\\"build\\\"\",\n    \"postbuild\": \"echo \\\"postbuild\\\"\"\n  },\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n}\n",[41,963,964,968,972,978,998,1017,1035,1039,1043],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,965,966],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,967,241],{"class":240},[149,969,970],{"class":151,"line":244},[149,971,664],{"class":663},[149,973,974,976],{"class":151,"line":260},[149,975,302],{"class":247},[149,977,305],{"class":240},[149,979,980,983,985,987,989,991,993,996],{"class":151,"line":273},[149,981,982],{"class":247},"    \"prebuild\"",[149,984,251],{"class":240},[149,986,316],{"class":159},[149,988,320],{"class":319},[149,990,929],{"class":159},[149,992,320],{"class":319},[149,994,995],{"class":159},"\"",[149,997,257],{"class":240},[149,999,1000,1003,1005,1007,1009,1011,1013,1015],{"class":151,"line":286},[149,1001,1002],{"class":247},"    \"build\"",[149,1004,251],{"class":240},[149,1006,316],{"class":159},[149,1008,320],{"class":319},[149,1010,932],{"class":159},[149,1012,320],{"class":319},[149,1014,995],{"class":159},[149,1016,257],{"class":240},[149,1018,1019,1022,1024,1026,1028,1030,1032],{"class":151,"line":299},[149,1020,1021],{"class":247},"    \"postbuild\"",[149,1023,251],{"class":240},[149,1025,316],{"class":159},[149,1027,320],{"class":319},[149,1029,935],{"class":159},[149,1031,320],{"class":319},[149,1033,1034],{"class":159},"\"\n",[149,1036,1037],{"class":151,"line":308},[149,1038,334],{"class":240},[149,1040,1041],{"class":151,"line":331},[149,1042,664],{"class":663},[149,1044,1045],{"class":151,"line":337},[149,1046,372],{"class":240},[12,1048,1049],{},[15,1050],{"alt":1051,"src":1052},"Life Cycle","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fnpm_build_life.png",[111,1054,1055],{},[12,1056,1057,1059,1062,1063,1066],{},[116,1058,118],{},[41,1060,1061],{},"echo"," is a command that displays text in the terminal — e.g., ",[41,1064,1065],{},"echo \"Hello World\""," displays \"Hello World\".",[12,1068,1069,1070,849,1073,1076,1077,1079,1080,1082,1083,1086,1087,1090,1091,1096,1097,1099],{},"What's \"Life Cycle Operation Order\" useful for? For example, if you want to do something before Build, you can use ",[41,1071,1072],{},"pre-",[41,1074,1075],{},"post-"," prefixes. These are called \"",[41,1078,1072],{},"\" and \"",[41,1081,1075],{},"\" events. In practice, the most common one is ",[41,1084,1085],{},"postinstall"," — running something after package install (",[41,1088,1089],{},"npm install","). For instance, in my earlier post ",[614,1092,1095],{"href":1093,"rel":1094},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fnodejs\u002F20201229\u002F1974873838\u002F",[618],"Auto-generating API docs with Swagger (article in Mandarin)",", I needed to auto-generate API docs after install — that's where ",[41,1098,1085],{}," comes in:",[140,1101,1103],{"className":231,"code":1102,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"postinstall\": \"node .\u002Fswagger.js\"\n  },\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n}\n",[41,1104,1105,1109,1113,1119,1129,1133,1137],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,1106,1107],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,1108,241],{"class":240},[149,1110,1111],{"class":151,"line":244},[149,1112,664],{"class":663},[149,1114,1115,1117],{"class":151,"line":260},[149,1116,302],{"class":247},[149,1118,305],{"class":240},[149,1120,1121,1124,1126],{"class":151,"line":273},[149,1122,1123],{"class":247},"    \"postinstall\"",[149,1125,251],{"class":240},[149,1127,1128],{"class":159},"\"node .\u002Fswagger.js\"\n",[149,1130,1131],{"class":151,"line":286},[149,1132,334],{"class":240},[149,1134,1135],{"class":151,"line":299},[149,1136,664],{"class":663},[149,1138,1139],{"class":151,"line":308},[149,1140,372],{"class":240},[12,1142,1143,1145],{},[41,1144,574],{}," can also be written like this:",[140,1147,1149],{"className":231,"code":1148,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"postinstall\": \"npm run swagger\",\n    \"swagger-autogen\": \"node .\u002Fswagger.js\"\n  },\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n}\n",[41,1150,1151,1155,1159,1165,1176,1185,1189,1193],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,1152,1153],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,1154,241],{"class":240},[149,1156,1157],{"class":151,"line":244},[149,1158,664],{"class":663},[149,1160,1161,1163],{"class":151,"line":260},[149,1162,302],{"class":247},[149,1164,305],{"class":240},[149,1166,1167,1169,1171,1174],{"class":151,"line":273},[149,1168,1123],{"class":247},[149,1170,251],{"class":240},[149,1172,1173],{"class":159},"\"npm run swagger\"",[149,1175,257],{"class":240},[149,1177,1178,1181,1183],{"class":151,"line":286},[149,1179,1180],{"class":247},"    \"swagger-autogen\"",[149,1182,251],{"class":240},[149,1184,1128],{"class":159},[149,1186,1187],{"class":151,"line":299},[149,1188,334],{"class":240},[149,1190,1191],{"class":151,"line":308},[149,1192,664],{"class":663},[149,1194,1195],{"class":151,"line":331},[149,1196,372],{"class":240},[12,1198,1199,1200,703],{},"For multiple commands, you can use ",[41,1201,1202],{},"&&",[140,1204,1206],{"className":231,"code":1205,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"postinstall\": \"npm run swagger && npm run gulp\",\n    \"swagger-autogen\": \"node .\u002Fswagger.js\",\n    \"gulp\": \"echo \\\"gulp\\\"\"\n  },\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n}\n",[41,1207,1208,1212,1216,1222,1233,1244,1262,1266,1270],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,1209,1210],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,1211,241],{"class":240},[149,1213,1214],{"class":151,"line":244},[149,1215,664],{"class":663},[149,1217,1218,1220],{"class":151,"line":260},[149,1219,302],{"class":247},[149,1221,305],{"class":240},[149,1223,1224,1226,1228,1231],{"class":151,"line":273},[149,1225,1123],{"class":247},[149,1227,251],{"class":240},[149,1229,1230],{"class":159},"\"npm run swagger && npm run gulp\"",[149,1232,257],{"class":240},[149,1234,1235,1237,1239,1242],{"class":151,"line":286},[149,1236,1180],{"class":247},[149,1238,251],{"class":240},[149,1240,1241],{"class":159},"\"node .\u002Fswagger.js\"",[149,1243,257],{"class":240},[149,1245,1246,1249,1251,1253,1255,1258,1260],{"class":151,"line":299},[149,1247,1248],{"class":247},"    \"gulp\"",[149,1250,251],{"class":240},[149,1252,316],{"class":159},[149,1254,320],{"class":319},[149,1256,1257],{"class":159},"gulp",[149,1259,320],{"class":319},[149,1261,1034],{"class":159},[149,1263,1264],{"class":151,"line":308},[149,1265,334],{"class":240},[149,1267,1268],{"class":151,"line":331},[149,1269,664],{"class":663},[149,1271,1272],{"class":151,"line":337},[149,1273,372],{"class":240},[12,1275,1276,1277,1280,1281,1283],{},"This runs ",[41,1278,1279],{},"swagger-autogen"," then ",[41,1282,1257],{}," in order.",[12,1285,1286,1288,1289,815],{},[41,1287,574],{}," has tons more, so I won't cover them all. If you want to know more, check the ",[614,1290,1293],{"href":1291,"rel":1292},"https:\u002F\u002Fdocs.npmjs.com\u002Fcli\u002Fv9\u002Fusing-npm\u002Fscripts",[618],"official npm scripts docs",[20,1295,1297],{"id":1296},"what-about-package-lockjson","What about package-lock.json?",[12,1299,1300],{},"Surprised? Just package.json alone has tons of stuff to cover. So… what about package-lock.json?",[12,1302,1303,1304,1306,1307,1309],{},"package-lock.json is only generated when you run ",[41,1305,1089],{},". This file records detailed package version info. The benefit is that when you run ",[41,1308,1089],{}," in different environments (e.g., different computers), it installs based on the versions in package-lock.json — avoiding the issue of different versions being installed in different environments and breaking the project.",[12,1311,1312],{},"But wait — we said earlier that packages are installed based on versions in package.json. So why do we need package-lock.json? Isn't that redundant?",[12,1314,1315,1316,1318,1319,1322],{},"A real example might make this clearer. We just installed ",[41,1317,381],{}," with ",[41,1320,1321],{},"npm install nodemon",". Currently package.json looks like:",[140,1324,1326],{"className":231,"code":1325,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \"name\": \"example\",\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"nodemon\": \"^3.0.1\"\n  }\n}\n",[41,1327,1328,1332,1342,1346,1352,1360,1364],{"__ignoreMap":145},[149,1329,1330],{"class":151,"line":152},[149,1331,241],{"class":240},[149,1333,1334,1336,1338,1340],{"class":151,"line":244},[149,1335,248],{"class":247},[149,1337,251],{"class":240},[149,1339,254],{"class":159},[149,1341,257],{"class":240},[149,1343,1344],{"class":151,"line":260},[149,1345,664],{"class":663},[149,1347,1348,1350],{"class":151,"line":273},[149,1349,507],{"class":247},[149,1351,305],{"class":240},[149,1353,1354,1356,1358],{"class":151,"line":286},[149,1355,515],{"class":247},[149,1357,251],{"class":240},[149,1359,520],{"class":159},[149,1361,1362],{"class":151,"line":299},[149,1363,526],{"class":240},[149,1365,1366],{"class":151,"line":308},[149,1367,372],{"class":240},[12,1369,1370,1371,703],{},"But when you open package-lock.json, you'll find it's super long. Let's focus on ",[41,1372,381],{},[140,1374,1376],{"className":231,"code":1375,"language":233,"meta":145,"style":145},"{\n  \"name\": \"example\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"lockfileVersion\": 2,\n  \"requires\": true,\n  \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \u002F\u002F ...other properties omitted\n    \"nodemon\": {\n      \"version\": \"3.0.1\",\n      \"resolved\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fregistry.npmjs.org\u002Fnodemon\u002F-\u002Fnodemon-3.0.1.tgz\",\n      \"integrity\": \"sha512-g9AZ7HmkhQkqXkRc20w+ZfQ73cHLbE8hnPbtaFbFtCumZsjyMhKk9LajQ07U5Ux28lvFjZ5X7HvWR1xzU8jHVw==\",\n      \"requires\": {\n        \"chokidar\": \"^3.5.2\",\n        \"debug\": \"^3.2.7\",\n        \"ignore-by-default\": \"^1.0.1\",\n        \"minimatch\": \"^3.1.2\",\n        \"pstree.remy\"